<div id="Package">
<h2>Package signature for <em>[% pack.title FILTER html %] [%+ pack.version %]</em></h2>
<p class="text">This is the package signature as generated by
<a href="http://www.gnupg.org/" title="The GNU Privacy Guard">The GnuPG</a>.
This signature identifies the party that created the package. By verifying it
you are sure that the package coming from a trustworty person or organization.</p>
<p class="text">Here is the package signature:</p>
<pre><strong>[% pack.filesign %]</strong></pre>
<p class="text">You can save this signature in a text file (<em>e.g.&nbsp;
[% pack.filename %].asc</em>) in the same directory where the package file
(<em>[% pack.filename %]</em>) resides and you can verify it by issuing the
following command:</p>
<pre>gpg --verify [% pack.filename %].asc</pre>
<p class="text">NOTE: You need to import my <a href="ftp://sotirov-bg.net/KEY">
public key</a> first:</p>
<pre>gpg --import KEY</pre>
</div>

